ndgain-id_heal_06-raw.def:
Description: Commonly used indicator of the capacity to control infectious diseases. The indicator is a proportion of the population with access to excreta disposal facilities that can effectively prevent human, animal, and insect contact with excreta. 
Rationale: Sanitation influences the incidence of infectious diseases (Tol et al., 2007). Thus, access to sanitation is particularly crucial to build up preparedness to various natural disasters exacerbated by climate change (McMichael & Woodruff, 2005; Keim, 2008).
ndgain-id_heal_06-raw.name: Access to improved sanitation facilities
ndgain-id_heal_06-raw.source: Improved sanitation facilities (% of population with access), WDI
